      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do I need to disclose a failing retaining wall when selling in Queensland?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Under Queensland's Mandatory Seller Disclosure Statement requirements, sellers must disclose known material facts that could affect a buyer's decision to purchase. A retaining wall that is visibly failing, has been identified as requiring repair, or presents a risk of collapse is a material condition of the property. Failing to disclose a known retaining wall issue can give a buyer grounds for a compensation claim after settlement. The disclosure obligation applies to facts you know, not to defects you are unaware of."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does it cost to repair or replace a retaining wall in Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
